The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has announced 64 new positive cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) in the country. NCDC disclosed this in a tweet on Monday night, bringing the total number of confirmed cases in Nigeria to 1337. The tweet reads, “64 new cases of #COVID19 reported; 34-Lagos
15-FCT
11-Borno
2-Taraba
2-Gombe “As at 11:20pm 27th April- 1337 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. Discharged: 255
Deaths: 40. “One case previously reported as a Lagos State case, is now reported as an FCT case. “The total number of confirmed cases in Lagos is now at 764 and 157 in FCT.”  